"{\"uid\": \"thedailybeast.com-obsessed-celine-dion-return-stuns-at-bonkers-paris-olympics-opening-ceremony\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Senior Editor, Obsessed  A greatOlympics opening ceremonyshould be a profound, stirring celebration of a country's history and culture.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 135, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It should also be absolutely batshit.\", \"from\": 136, \"to\": 173, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"On those metrics, I would consider Friday's kickoff to the Paris games a rousing success.\", \"from\": 174, \"to\": 263, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 233, \"end\": 238, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.0892781336154896e-21, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The spectacle was, from my perspective, very French: I did not understand most of what was going on, but kept being aggressively told it was all very cool and so I convinced myself that I loved it.\", \"from\": 265, \"to\": 462, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"And then there was the C\\u00e9line Dion of it all.\", \"from\": 463, \"to\": 508, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"(Not French, but can speak it!)\", \"from\": 509, \"to\": 540, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I could never have-even on my most potent cocktail of melatonin, weed gummy, and white wine-dreamed up the orgy of music, dance styles, and energetic skipping through the streets of Paris that made up the eclectic ceremony.\", \"from\": 542, \"to\": 765, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 724, \"end\": 729, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.0892781336154896e-21, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The can-can!\", \"from\": 767, \"to\": 779, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Parkour!\", \"from\": 780, \"to\": 788, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"A queerm\\u00e9nage \\u00e0 troisin a library!Les Mis\\u00e9rables!\", \"from\": 789, \"to\": 838, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"A nonbinary masked individual riding a horse.\", \"from\": 839, \"to\": 884, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"A choir of beheaded Marie Antoinettes singing in windows while a heavy metal plays and fire rages.\", \"from\": 885, \"to\": 983, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"An Olympic torch that resembled a giant blunt, or maybe a flaming baguette.\", \"from\": 984, \"to\": 1059, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"A hot air balloon cauldron that looked like it was about to float on over to Oz.\", \"from\": 1060, \"to\": 1140, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The Minions???\", \"from\": 1141, \"to\": 1155, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"This#OpeningCeremonyhas everything.\", \"from\": 1157, \"to\": 1192, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Boats.\", \"from\": 1193, \"to\": 1199, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Parkour.\", \"from\": 1200, \"to\": 1208, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Accordians.\", \"from\": 1209, \"to\": 1220, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"A woman dressed as a croissant.\", \"from\": 1221, \"to\": 1252, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"More boats.\", \"from\": 1253, \"to\": 1264, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Lady Gaga.pic.twitter.com/asclWZwTNi  But the twin highlights of the affair seemed incepted from my dreams entirely: rousing performances byLady GagaandC\\u00e9line Dion, in her triumphant return to singing on a major stage after battling a rare autoimmune neurological disorder.\", \"from\": 1265, \"to\": 1538, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Dion was a reward for anyone who sat through four hours of a decidedly bonkers fantasia.\", \"from\": 1540, \"to\": 1628, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"After watching thousands and thousands of athletes being dragged through the Seine looking like drowned rats while skateboarders dressed as clowns did tricks in the background, there she was.\", \"from\": 1629, \"to\": 1820, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1706, \"end\": 1711, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.1835692293096654e-17, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In a blissfully dramatic fashion befitting Dion's stage persona, first you heard her voice, a gold-medal belt that has not been projected with that force publicly in years.\", \"from\": 1822, \"to\": 1994, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I got instant chills.\", \"from\": 1995, \"to\": 2016, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Then the camera zoomed in on the Eiffel Tower, dazzling with twinkling lights, to reveal Dion on a makeshift stage floating in the middle of the landmark.\", \"from\": 2017, \"to\": 2171, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"She looked positively regal in a beaded, sparkling white evening gown, her hair pulled back into a bun.\", \"from\": 2173, \"to\": 2276, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"She gesticulated muscularly while she hit each note.\", \"from\": 2277, \"to\": 2329, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"With two speakers flanking her, the image immediately evoked Eva Peron on her balcony-or, if you are gay like me, Patti LuPone singing \\\"Do not Cry for Me Argentina\\\" inEvita.\", \"from\": 2330, \"to\": 2503, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2391, \"end\": 2400, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eva_Per\\u00f3n\", \"score\": 0.999999983064754, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Eva Peron\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eva_Per\\u00f3n\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eva_Per\\u00f3n\"}, {\"begin\": 2444, \"end\": 2456, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Patti_LuPone\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Patti LuPone\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Patti_LuPone\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Patti_LuPone\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"During an instrumental break, she gazed out at the City of Light before her, from her ascendant position in one of the world's most iconic landmarks.\", \"from\": 2505, \"to\": 2654, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Tears welled in her eyes, echoing the raindrops splashing on the piano beside her.\", \"from\": 2655, \"to\": 2737, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I can not imagine what it must have felt like for her to make a comeback in such a monumental way-not just a return to the stage, but a return to a stage on the Eiffel Tower with the world watching.\", \"from\": 2738, \"to\": 2936, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I actually can not talk,\\\" announcer Kelly Clarkson said after the performance, clearly through her own tears.\", \"from\": 2938, \"to\": 3048, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"To have that moment.\", \"from\": 3049, \"to\": 3070, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"She's a vocal athlete.\", \"from\": 3071, \"to\": 3093, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"She's incredible.\\\"\", \"from\": 3094, \"to\": 3112, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It was an emotional finale that elevated a weird day of tons of rain, unusual performances, and, in true Olympic fashion, irresistible moments of inspiration and talent.\", \"from\": 3114, \"to\": 3283, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Earlier in the ceremony, which seems a lifetime ago at this point, Lady Gaga was a surprise performer-in that she was not on the official media guide, and yet everyone in the world knew that she was performing by the time she descended those stairs.\", \"from\": 3285, \"to\": 3534, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3352, \"end\": 3361, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lady_Gaga\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Lady Gaga\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lady_Gaga\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lady_Gaga\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She opened the show doing what I can only assume is a French translation ofSeussical, shaking a feathered tail with plumes shooting out of her hair and serving Mayzie LaBird realness.\", \"from\": 3535, \"to\": 3718, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3589, \"end\": 3595, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9982626081498432, \"rank\": 0.001740405753553946, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"If you do not understand that reference, I am both sorry that you have a blindspot for an underrated piece of musical theater culture-and also that you probably could not appreciate just how unabashedly gay so much of the ceremony was.\", \"from\": 3720, \"to\": 3955, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"(I mean\\u2026 there was a choreographed dance of giant Louis Vuitton trunks.)\", \"from\": 3956, \"to\": 4028, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4006, \"end\": 4019, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Louis_Vuitton\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.954322716139075e-34, \"text\": \"Louis Vuitton\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Louis_Vuitton\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Louis_Vuitton\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Gaga nailed every shimmy and shake, clearly having the time of her life belting out the French classic \\\"Mon Truc en Plumes,\\\" which translates to \\\"My Thing With Feathers.\\\"\", \"from\": 4030, \"to\": 4200, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4030, \"end\": 4034, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lady_Gaga\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.6945276710678682e-52, \"text\": \"Gaga\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lady_Gaga\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lady_Gaga\"}, {\"begin\": 4118, \"end\": 4132, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Classic_Races\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"French classic\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Classic_Races\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Classic_Races\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Is it strange that the Paris Olympics chose an Italian American pop star to open their show?\", \"from\": 4201, \"to\": 4293, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4248, \"end\": 4264, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italian_Americans\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.933580445687603e-18, \"text\": \"Italian American\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italian_Americans\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italian_Americans\"}, {\"begin\": 4248, \"end\": 4264, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italian_Americans\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.933580445687603e-18, \"text\": \"Italian American\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italian_Americans\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italian_Americans\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Or is it brilliant?\", \"from\": 4294, \"to\": 4313, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The MVP of any televised ceremony is always going to be Lady Gaga.\", \"from\": 4314, \"to\": 4380, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4318, \"end\": 4321, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Most_valuable_player\", \"score\": 0.9995586234815447, \"rank\": 0.00024568171444077383, \"text\": \"MVP\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Most_valuable_player\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Most_valuable_player\"}, {\"begin\": 4370, \"end\": 4379, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lady_Gaga\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Lady Gaga\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lady_Gaga\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lady_Gaga\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"(Plus, she sang some of \\\"La Vie en Rose\\\" inA Star Is Born, which makes her canonically French in my world.)\", \"from\": 4381, \"to\": 4488, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Lady Gaga performing at the Paris Olympics opening ceremony.\", \"from\": 4490, \"to\": 4550, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4490, \"end\": 4499, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lady_Gaga\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Lady Gaga\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lady_Gaga\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lady_Gaga\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Watching the opening ceremony was, as always, a surreal experience: the horny thrill every time they showed Emmanuel Macron; the desire to call the head of every TV network immediately and beg them to have Kelly Clarkson offer running commentary to every live event.\", \"from\": 4552, \"to\": 4818, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4660, \"end\": 4675, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Emmanuel Macron\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\"}, {\"begin\": 4758, \"end\": 4772, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kelly_Clarkson\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Kelly Clarkson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kelly_Clarkson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kelly_Clarkson\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I laughed along to Gaga's cheekiness.\", \"from\": 4820, \"to\": 4857, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4839, \"end\": 4843, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lady_Gaga\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.6945276710678682e-52, \"text\": \"Gaga\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lady_Gaga\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lady_Gaga\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I stared bewildered at 90 percent of the dance routines.\", \"from\": 4858, \"to\": 4914, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I cried as C\\u00e9line sang.\", \"from\": 4915, \"to\": 4938, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I feared for the competitors' safety: One thing every athlete should do on the eve of the biggest physical contest of their lives is take a three-hour evening boat ride in the pouring rain.\", \"from\": 4939, \"to\": 5128, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I learned that you can, apparently, get seasick from watching boats bob up and down on TV.\", \"from\": 5129, \"to\": 5219, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"And, most importantly, I got stoked for the next two weeks of making the Olympics my entire personality.\", \"from\": 5221, \"to\": 5325, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Senior Editor, Obsessed  kevin.fallon@thedailybeast.com  Got a tip?\", \"from\": 5327, \"to\": 5394, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Send it to The Daily Beasthere.\", \"from\": 5395, \"to\": 5426, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"ADVERTISEMENT  ADVERTISEMENT\", \"from\": 5428, \"to\": 5456, \"entities\": []}]}"